{"title":"Overview","markdown":{"headingText":"Overview","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":["unnumbered"],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\nThese labs provide a unique opportunity to gain practical experience with machine learning (ML) systems. Unlike working with large models requiring data center-scale resources, these exercises allow you to directly interact with hardware and software using TinyML. This hands-on approach gives you a tangible understanding of the challenges and opportunities in deploying AI, albeit at a tiny scale. However, the principles are largely the same as what you would encounter when working with larger systems.\n\n![Nicla Vision. Source: Arduino.](./images/jpg/nicla_vision_quarter.jpeg){width=70%}\n\n## Where to Buy {#sec-overview-where-to-buy}\n\nThe Arduino Nicla Vision is available from the official Arduino Store:\n\n- [Arduino Store](https://store.arduino.cc/products/nicla-vision) (~$95)\n\n## Pre-requisites {#sec-overview-prerequisites-b2d4}\n\n- **Nicla Vision Board**: Ensure you have the Nicla Vision board.\n- **USB Cable**: For connecting the board to your computer.\n- **Network**: With internet access for downloading necessary software.\n\n## Setup {#sec-overview-setup-cde0}\n\n- [Setup Nicla Vision](@sec-setup-overview-dcdd)\n\n## Exercises {#sec-overview-exercises-f4f3}\n\n| **Modality** | **Task** | **Description** | **Link** |\n|:--------------|:--------------|:-----------------|:----------|\n| Vision       | Image Classification | Learn to classify images | [Link](@sec-image-classification-overview-7420) |\n| Vision       | Object Detection     | Implement object detection | [Link](@sec-object-detection-overview-9d59) |\n| Sound        | Keyword Spotting                   | Explore voice recognition systems         | [Link](@sec-keyword-spotting-kws-overview-0ae6)                  |\n| IMU          | Motion Classification and Anomaly Detection | Classify motion data and detect anomalies | [Link](@sec-motion-cl